  "fun_fact": "Before synthetic dyes took over in the 19th century, every colour humans used came from the natural world — plants, minerals, insects, and shells. India was a global hub for natural dyes, with indigo and lac traded across continents for centuries. Today, as synthetic dyes pollute rivers and harm ecosystems, natural dyes are making a quiet comeback in sustainable fashion and traditional crafts.",
